Resources

wiicopter; description on how to mod wiicontroller to use the gyro and accelerometer
http://radio-commande.com/international/triwiicopter-design/

diy page on quadras. lots of info?
http://www.scoutuav.com

blog on how to make your first quadra. provides good overview?
http://oddcopter.com/2012/12/12/easy-diy-quadcopter-build-part-1-the-parts-list/

blog post listing five good resources on how to build a quadra
http://www.intorobotics.com/5-best-examples-of-how-to-build-a-diy-quadcopter/

more detailed resource for beginners on most aspects of how to build copters
http://copter.ardupilot.com/wiki/build-your-own-multicopter/

very good, more technical, blog post on how to build a quadra
http://blog.oscarliang.net/build-a-quadcopter-beginners-tutorial-1/

technical post on choice of battery
http://robot-kingdom.com/what-battery-should-you-use-on-your-robot/

technical website on hobby aviation
http://www.stefanv.com/electronics/escprimer.html

online store providing quadracopter parts and kits
http://www.hobbyking.com/hobbyking/store/index.asp

technical resource about magnetics and how to construct motors and speed controllers
http://www.consult-g2.com/course.html

post with some lins to resources on motors and speed controllers
http://www.rcgroups.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=140454

